    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Style and culture of a Native American tribe in central North Carolina. Descended primarily from Occaneechi communities that have lived in the area since European contact; Eno, Saponi, and other Siouan-speaking tribes also comprise modern Occaneechi identity. </Note_Text>
